</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BADC92BFFBF5723FF6894307869043A" blockId="14.[151,1437,1356,1960]" pageId="14" pageNumber="459">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBF5723FF6894307C1A0466" bold="true" box="[199,369,1572,1599]" pageId="14" pageNumber="459">Digestive tube</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBF5723FE2D94317CB10466" box="[386,474,1573,1599]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1970,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1309,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-259@12.[151,1435,1309,1945]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 14. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, gizzard; b, enteric valve." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571701/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="459">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1329D5AEFFBF5723FE4894317F210419" box="[487,586,1573,1600]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1981,2005]" captionTargetBox="[163,1435,601,1957]" captionTargetId="figure-247@13.[151,1436,597,1958]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 15. Worker gut of Bandeiratermes silvestrii. a, dorsal; b, left; c, ventral; d, right view; e, detail of the mesenteron-P1 junction and Malpighian tubules; f, worker mandibles in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571703/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="459">15a–15e</figureCitation>
). As described for the genus, the gut conformation is the same as 
<taxonomicName id="4C12B2A8FFBF5723FA9594327DB6043A" authorityName="Constantino" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" genus="Ibitermes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="14" pageNumber="459" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tellustris">
<emphasis id="B9661539FFBF5723FA9594327DB6043A" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="459">Ban. tellustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing only in size (slightly larger) and by the mesenteric tongue width (slightly narrower).
</paragraph>
